  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If `block.number >= METROPOLIS_FORK_BLKNUM`, then opcode `0xfa` functions equivalently to a `CALL`, except it takes 6 arguments not including value, and calls the child with a `STATIC` flag on. Any calls, static or otherwise, made by an execution instance with a `STATIC` flag on will also have a `STATIC` flag on. Any attempts to make state-changing operations inside an execution instance with a `STATIC` flag on, including nonzero-value calls, creates, and `SSTORE`, `SSTOREBYTES` or `SUICIDE` operations, will instead throw an exception.\n### Rationale\n\nThis allows contracts to make calls that are clearly non-state-changing, reassuring developers and reviewers that re-entrancy bugs or other problems cannot possibly arise from that particular call; it is a pure function that returns an output and does nothing else. This may also make purely functional HLLs easier to implement.\n",
